1
00:00:07,125 --> 00:00:08,418
YUTY: It can't be!

2
00:00:08,418 --> 00:00:09,836
‐ Frenzy.

3
00:00:09,836 --> 00:00:12,422
[Bellcross roars]

4
00:00:13,798 --> 00:00:17,218
‐ What does he hope
to accomplish?

5
00:00:17,218 --> 00:00:18,511
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

6
00:00:18,511 --> 00:00:22,390
‐ I have... no choice.

7
00:00:22,390 --> 00:00:24,309
I must.

8
00:00:26,019 --> 00:00:28,021
‐ This is not Age.

9
00:00:28,021 --> 00:00:31,358
He would never do
these awful things.

10
00:00:31,358 --> 00:00:33,109
Never.

11
00:00:33,109 --> 00:00:38,615
Something has come over him,
something he cannot control.

12
00:00:38,615 --> 00:00:41,201
It's up to us.

13
00:00:41,201 --> 00:00:43,411
We must save our savior.

14
00:00:43,411 --> 00:00:46,414
<i>["Gravitation" by Angela]</i>

15
00:00:46,414 --> 00:00:49,501
[woman singing in Japanese]

16
00:02:23,845 --> 00:02:26,848
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

17
00:02:26,848 --> 00:02:33,897
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18
00:02:35,690 --> 00:02:38,985
MAN: The frenzied Nodos
is unstoppable.

19
00:02:38,985 --> 00:02:41,029
MAN:
They will destroy all of them.

20
00:02:41,029 --> 00:02:43,364
MAN: The situation
is out of our hands.

21
00:02:43,364 --> 00:02:45,116
We must withdraw.

22
00:02:46,951 --> 00:02:49,245
‐ We will not withdraw.

23
00:02:49,245 --> 00:02:51,372
Our Nodos requires help.

24
00:02:51,372 --> 00:02:53,750
We will fight at his side.

25
00:02:53,750 --> 00:02:56,544
Put everything we've got
into those sectors.

26
00:02:56,544 --> 00:02:59,255
Finish this once and for all!

27
00:03:08,973 --> 00:03:12,560
[Bellcross roaring]

28
00:03:26,533 --> 00:03:29,577
<i>[intense music]</i>

29
00:03:29,577 --> 00:03:36,584
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30
00:03:51,391 --> 00:03:58,398
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31
00:04:09,492 --> 00:04:11,452
NILVAL:
Hold the line as best you can.

32
00:04:11,452 --> 00:04:13,121
Help is on the way.

33
00:04:13,121 --> 00:04:15,874
‐ The destruction of the planet
is inevitable,

34
00:04:15,874 --> 00:04:18,626
and I'm afraid the Starway
is still far too unstable

35
00:04:18,626 --> 00:04:20,962
to support the passage
of our reinforcements.

36
00:04:20,962 --> 00:04:23,464
‐ Oh, don't you worry
about that.

37
00:04:23,464 --> 00:04:25,717
The "Argonaut"
is an exceptional ship.

38
00:04:25,717 --> 00:04:27,302
MAN:
More survivors are trickling in.

39
00:04:27,302 --> 00:04:28,720
They're requesting to join us.

40
00:04:28,720 --> 00:04:29,846
‐ Have their ships aligned

41
00:04:29,846 --> 00:04:31,014
to our current orbit.

42
00:04:31,014 --> 00:04:33,016
We'll pick them all up en route.

43
00:04:33,016 --> 00:04:34,434
Contact
as many of the missing

44
00:04:34,434 --> 00:04:35,852
fleet members as you can.

45
00:04:35,852 --> 00:04:37,979
Alert everyone
to the reorganization.

46
00:04:37,979 --> 00:04:40,732
‐ Wait. Lieutenant General,
this doesn't look good.

47
00:04:40,732 --> 00:04:42,400
I'm picking up
the presence of something

48
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:44,527
whose total energy output
is catastrophic.

49
00:04:44,527 --> 00:04:46,446
‐ Our AI system
has located the source

50
00:04:46,446 --> 00:04:49,073
as a nearby star
about to go supernova.

51
00:04:49,073 --> 00:04:52,785
We have approximately 100 hours
before it hits critical mass!

52
00:04:52,785 --> 00:04:55,538
‐ It's impossible
for a star to go supernova

53
00:04:55,538 --> 00:04:56,831
in that span of time.

54
00:04:56,831 --> 00:04:58,082
Recheck the data!

55
00:04:58,082 --> 00:04:59,792
Find out what's causing it!

56
00:04:59,792 --> 00:05:01,419
MAN: Judging from the stats
we've collected

57
00:05:01,419 --> 00:05:03,963
over the course of this battle,
the only other explanation

58
00:05:03,963 --> 00:05:05,173
would be the Nodos itself.

59
00:05:05,173 --> 00:05:06,841
MAN:
Its energy output is increasing

60
00:05:06,841 --> 00:05:08,343
exponentially and fast.

61
00:05:08,343 --> 00:05:09,677
If this continues unabated,

62
00:05:09,677 --> 00:05:12,305
the whole solar system
will be destroyed!

63
00:05:12,305 --> 00:05:15,225
‐ It... can't...

64
00:05:15,225 --> 00:05:16,643
MAN: That can't be right.

65
00:05:16,643 --> 00:05:18,186
Recalibrate the data.

66
00:05:18,186 --> 00:05:21,606
MAN: But sir, AI recalibrates
the data automatically.

67
00:05:21,606 --> 00:05:24,859
MAN: Confound it, man.
Do it manually!

68
00:05:24,859 --> 00:05:27,111
‐ There's no chance in hell
we can get everyone

69
00:05:27,111 --> 00:05:29,405
out of harm's way in time.

70
00:05:29,405 --> 00:05:31,366
The whole damn system
is about to blow,

71
00:05:31,366 --> 00:05:33,034
and we've got front row tickets.

72
00:05:33,034 --> 00:05:34,869
MAN: Are you sure
there hasn't been a mistake?

73
00:05:34,869 --> 00:05:36,371
MAN:
We've checked and rechecked.

74
00:05:36,371 --> 00:05:37,705
There's no mistake.

75
00:05:37,705 --> 00:05:39,415
AI keeps spitting out
the same warning.

76
00:05:39,415 --> 00:05:42,293
The data is correct.

77
00:05:42,293 --> 00:05:43,836
‐ According to the legend,

78
00:05:43,836 --> 00:05:44,879
the only ones capable

79
00:05:44,879 --> 00:05:46,464
of placating a heroic fury

80
00:05:46,464 --> 00:05:49,259
were the Golden Tribe
themselves.

81
00:05:49,259 --> 00:05:51,552
That doesn't bode very well
for us.

82
00:05:51,552 --> 00:05:55,014
How could we possibly hope
to stop him?

83
00:05:56,349 --> 00:05:58,851
So, then,
it seems that our hopes

84
00:05:58,851 --> 00:06:01,646
were foolish after all.

85
00:06:04,232 --> 00:06:07,443
Contact the "Argonaut"
immediately.

86
00:06:07,443 --> 00:06:09,821
MAN:
Local gravity shock detected.

87
00:06:09,821 --> 00:06:11,072
‐ [gasps]

88
00:06:11,072 --> 00:06:14,158
[shimmering and tinkling]

89
00:06:20,498 --> 00:06:23,626
MAN: Allied fleets
converging on our position.

90
00:06:30,258 --> 00:06:33,094
‐ Look. They've made it through.

91
00:06:33,094 --> 00:06:37,056
‐ Unbelievable. They actually
navigated through the Starway.

92
00:06:37,056 --> 00:06:40,101
And in the middle
of such a huge battle, no less.

93
00:06:40,101 --> 00:06:42,603
‐ I hate to say "I told you so,"
Lieutenant,

94
00:06:42,603 --> 00:06:45,815
but the "Argonaut"
is an exceptional vessel.

95
00:06:45,815 --> 00:06:50,153
Here I am, putting
all of these people in jeopardy.

96
00:06:50,153 --> 00:06:53,614
I am unworthy of rescue.

97
00:06:53,614 --> 00:06:55,324
Put me through to them
right now.

98
00:06:55,324 --> 00:06:58,369
I will apologize to Princess
Dhianeila personally.

99
00:06:58,369 --> 00:07:00,872
DHIANEILA:
There is no need of that.

100
00:07:00,872 --> 00:07:03,541
You have shown
extraordinary courage, Nilval.

101
00:07:03,541 --> 00:07:06,294
It is I who should be
apologizing to you.

102
00:07:06,294 --> 00:07:09,255
Please, forgive me.

103
00:07:09,255 --> 00:07:11,174
‐ Princess Dhianeila, I‐‐

104
00:07:11,174 --> 00:07:13,384
‐ A great many brave ships
have gone missing

105
00:07:13,384 --> 00:07:14,969
in the course of this battle.

106
00:07:14,969 --> 00:07:17,638
Even so,
hope of their recovery is nigh.

107
00:07:17,638 --> 00:07:20,266
Their presence
isn't lost to me yet.

108
00:07:22,852 --> 00:07:25,104
‐ Lieutenant General,
their positions are beginning

109
00:07:25,104 --> 00:07:28,316
to show up
on the telepathic line.

110
00:07:28,316 --> 00:07:31,986
‐ Princess... thank you, but‐‐

111
00:07:31,986 --> 00:07:34,572
DHIANEILA: Please, Nilval.

112
00:07:34,572 --> 00:07:37,325
We must keep hope alive.

113
00:07:37,325 --> 00:07:38,910
<i>♪ ♪</i>

114
00:07:38,910 --> 00:07:41,662
Have faith.
It's true that Age is capable

115
00:07:41,662 --> 00:07:44,373
of almost unthinkable
destruction,

116
00:07:44,373 --> 00:07:46,042
but I know his heart is pure,

117
00:07:46,042 --> 00:07:48,211
and at great peril to myself,

118
00:07:48,211 --> 00:07:49,587
I will prove it.

119
00:07:49,587 --> 00:07:51,089
‐ [gasps]

120
00:07:51,089 --> 00:07:53,007
‐ But I will not
put the fleet in danger

121
00:07:53,007 --> 00:07:54,759
while we are searching for him.

122
00:07:54,759 --> 00:07:57,845
The "Argonaut" will go alone.

123
00:07:57,845 --> 00:08:01,432
Therefore, I have to ask of you
and your crewmembers

124
00:08:01,432 --> 00:08:03,810
that you stay behind
and continue fighting

125
00:08:03,810 --> 00:08:06,979
for humanity's right to survive.

126
00:08:06,979 --> 00:08:09,148
<i>♪ ♪</i>

127
00:08:09,148 --> 00:08:10,775
‐ There is no path more arduous

128
00:08:10,775 --> 00:08:13,069
than the one
you yourself must follow.

129
00:08:13,069 --> 00:08:15,363
I swear my allegiance to you.

130
00:08:15,363 --> 00:08:16,614
Forever.

131
00:08:16,614 --> 00:08:19,033
I will defend the "Argonaut"
in your name,

132
00:08:19,033 --> 00:08:23,079
with every single fiber
of my being.

133
00:08:23,079 --> 00:08:24,872
‐ Thank you, Nilval,

134
00:08:24,872 --> 00:08:28,584
and may the wisdom of the stars
guide you.

135
00:08:30,419 --> 00:08:31,879
[alert whistles]

136
00:08:31,879 --> 00:08:34,215
MAN: I'm getting a transmission
from the "Argonaut."

137
00:08:34,215 --> 00:08:35,508
‐ Put it through.

138
00:08:35,508 --> 00:08:38,344
‐ Well,
there you have it, Nilval.

139
00:08:38,344 --> 00:08:40,555
Sorry to leave the battle
so early,

140
00:08:40,555 --> 00:08:42,140
but duty calls.

141
00:08:42,140 --> 00:08:44,892
The princess is trying to draw
as little attention to us

142
00:08:44,892 --> 00:08:46,519
as humanly possible.

143
00:08:46,519 --> 00:08:47,979
If you like,
you can have the honor

144
00:08:47,979 --> 00:08:49,939
of covering our butts
while we warp out

145
00:08:49,939 --> 00:08:53,443
of this little soiree.

146
00:08:53,443 --> 00:08:56,070
‐ All available ships
are to surround the "Argonaut"

147
00:08:56,070 --> 00:08:57,071
immediately.

148
00:08:57,071 --> 00:08:58,573
‐ Humph. Look at you.

149
00:08:58,573 --> 00:08:59,907
Here you are, at the brink

150
00:08:59,907 --> 00:09:02,702
of the most dangerous mission
of your career,

151
00:09:02,702 --> 00:09:04,996
and you're smiling
like a daydreamer.

152
00:09:04,996 --> 00:09:07,582
‐ I'm a very happy man
right now.

153
00:09:07,582 --> 00:09:10,042
Setting sail
for the great unknown,

154
00:09:10,042 --> 00:09:12,712
pitting my wits
against the universe‐‐

155
00:09:12,712 --> 00:09:15,298
who wouldn't be smiling?

156
00:09:15,298 --> 00:09:16,716
MAN: Recharge complete.

157
00:09:16,716 --> 00:09:18,009
Warp course confirmed.

158
00:09:18,009 --> 00:09:19,427
WOMAN: Establishing link.

159
00:09:19,427 --> 00:09:22,430
‐ Pleasure serving with you.
Over and out.

160
00:09:22,430 --> 00:09:24,640
<i>♪ ♪</i>

161
00:09:24,640 --> 00:09:27,268
WOMAN:
Horoscope acquisition confirmed.

162
00:09:27,268 --> 00:09:31,439
<i>♪ ♪</i>

163
00:09:31,439 --> 00:09:33,441
Suspending temporal functions.

164
00:09:33,441 --> 00:09:35,526
All sails down.

165
00:09:35,526 --> 00:09:38,488
Dimensional ripper activated.

166
00:09:38,488 --> 00:09:40,990
<i>♪ ♪</i>

167
00:09:40,990 --> 00:09:42,783
Max warp!

168
00:09:45,536 --> 00:09:48,623
[shimmering and tinkling]

169
00:10:01,135 --> 00:10:04,180
[debris shuffling]

170
00:10:25,493 --> 00:10:28,538
[space roaring]

171
00:10:40,174 --> 00:10:44,929
‐ The fifth Nodos...
he is frenzied.

172
00:10:44,929 --> 00:10:46,973
Artemia.

173
00:10:46,973 --> 00:10:50,017
Has Mehitak, too, gone mad?

174
00:10:51,018 --> 00:10:52,687
Lernaea moves.

175
00:10:52,687 --> 00:10:54,939
Will you fight
before fully regenerating,

176
00:10:54,939 --> 00:10:57,066
Karkinos?

177
00:10:57,066 --> 00:11:00,319
YUTY:
This is unacceptable, Lecty.

178
00:11:00,319 --> 00:11:03,864
A frenzied Nodos raging
through the galaxy unchecked.

179
00:11:03,864 --> 00:11:07,368
The three of you must put a stop
to this before it's too late.

180
00:11:07,368 --> 00:11:10,204
We cannot allow
for more worlds to be lost.

181
00:11:10,204 --> 00:11:12,123
‐ By fighting him
in such a state,

182
00:11:12,123 --> 00:11:15,376
we risk subjecting ourselves
to the same madness.

183
00:11:15,376 --> 00:11:18,129
The devastation
would be immeasurable.

184
00:11:18,129 --> 00:11:23,259
And the one most likely to die
is Karkinos.

185
00:11:23,259 --> 00:11:24,760
‐ What did you say?

186
00:11:24,760 --> 00:11:26,220
‐ It is a possibility.

187
00:11:26,220 --> 00:11:28,681
The likelihood is inferred
in his contract.

188
00:11:28,681 --> 00:11:31,684
If the Golden Tribe could indeed
foresee the future‐‐

189
00:11:31,684 --> 00:11:33,185
‐ The Golden Tribe
only predicted

190
00:11:33,185 --> 00:11:35,187
the number of Labors
in each contract.

191
00:11:35,187 --> 00:11:37,898
We are fools to surmise
anything else from them.

192
00:11:37,898 --> 00:11:41,027
‐ But Yuty, they were told
of the Iron Tribe.

193
00:11:41,027 --> 00:11:43,613
They knew
they would discover the fifth.

194
00:11:43,613 --> 00:11:46,324
‐ Karkinos is able to regenerate
from fatal wounds.

195
00:11:46,324 --> 00:11:48,743
Therefore, he is,
for all intents and purposes,

196
00:11:48,743 --> 00:11:49,785
immortal.

197
00:11:49,785 --> 00:11:51,037
A creature of that power

198
00:11:51,037 --> 00:11:52,747
has to be subjugated.

199
00:11:52,747 --> 00:11:53,914
Just think about it.

200
00:11:53,914 --> 00:11:55,249
This contract must deceive

201
00:11:55,249 --> 00:11:56,500
in order to be effective.

202
00:11:56,500 --> 00:11:59,420
‐ Even so,
what if all of us go mad?

203
00:11:59,420 --> 00:12:02,590
YUTY: Do not be concerned
with your own safety.

204
00:12:02,590 --> 00:12:04,800
Leave that to me.

205
00:12:04,800 --> 00:12:07,219
LECTY: I... understand.

206
00:12:07,219 --> 00:12:10,139
If such is the will
of the Silver Tribe,

207
00:12:10,139 --> 00:12:12,266
I shall obey.

208
00:12:13,934 --> 00:12:20,941
<i>♪ ♪</i>

209
00:12:28,741 --> 00:12:32,328
‐ If the four of them
succumb to the frenzy,

210
00:12:32,328 --> 00:12:34,955
you will not hesitate
to abolish them.

211
00:12:34,955 --> 00:12:35,873
‐ [gasps]

212
00:12:35,873 --> 00:12:37,458
‐ If I did not think you

213
00:12:37,458 --> 00:12:40,086
beyond such crude emotion,

214
00:12:40,086 --> 00:12:42,463
I might read
a suggestion of dread

215
00:12:42,463 --> 00:12:44,173
in that expression.

216
00:12:45,591 --> 00:12:48,219
‐ No. Not at all, sir.

217
00:12:48,219 --> 00:12:55,226
<i>♪ ♪</i>

218
00:13:01,065 --> 00:13:04,193
<i>[epic orchestral music]</i>

219
00:13:04,193 --> 00:13:11,242
<i>♪ ♪</i>

220
00:13:12,410 --> 00:13:15,496
[Bellcross roaring]

221
00:13:28,676 --> 00:13:34,598
<i>♪ ♪</i>

222
00:13:34,598 --> 00:13:36,392
MAN: We're obeying at our peril.

223
00:13:36,392 --> 00:13:38,561
MAN: There is no hope
that we shall survive

224
00:13:38,561 --> 00:13:40,938
the ruin that falls in his wake.

225
00:13:40,938 --> 00:13:42,940
‐ Victory is at hand.

226
00:13:42,940 --> 00:13:44,150
I feel it.

227
00:13:44,150 --> 00:13:46,485
MAN: We must withdraw.

228
00:13:46,485 --> 00:13:49,530
MAN: We have no other choice.

229
00:13:51,449 --> 00:13:53,617
‐ So be it.

230
00:13:59,707 --> 00:14:04,712
<i>♪ ♪</i>

231
00:14:10,593 --> 00:14:11,886
[Artemia cries out]

232
00:14:24,899 --> 00:14:27,943
[Artemia moans]

233
00:14:29,403 --> 00:14:36,452
<i>♪ ♪</i>

234
00:14:48,088 --> 00:14:55,137
<i>♪ ♪</i>

235
00:15:06,899 --> 00:15:13,906
<i>♪ ♪</i>

236
00:15:23,290 --> 00:15:26,377
[shimmering and tinkling]

237
00:15:35,386 --> 00:15:36,554
‐ All right!

238
00:15:36,554 --> 00:15:37,972
Now, let's show
this ugly bastard

239
00:15:37,972 --> 00:15:41,183
what it means to tangle
with the Yunos Knights!

240
00:15:45,896 --> 00:15:48,148
We've got to try
and hold this monster at bay.

241
00:15:48,148 --> 00:15:51,944
We can't let him get to Age
before the princess!

242
00:15:51,944 --> 00:15:56,949
<i>♪ ♪</i>

243
00:15:58,784 --> 00:16:00,327
YUTY: What are you doing?

244
00:16:00,327 --> 00:16:01,787
It's only the Iron Tribe.

245
00:16:01,787 --> 00:16:05,583
Why aren't you
assisting Karkinos?

246
00:16:05,583 --> 00:16:09,003
And why haven't you evoked
the power of Erymanthos?

247
00:16:09,003 --> 00:16:12,548
Go back, and destroy their ship.

248
00:16:12,548 --> 00:16:17,136
‐ I... I tried to,
and I can't.

249
00:16:17,136 --> 00:16:18,304
‐ Huh?

250
00:16:18,304 --> 00:16:20,431
‐ Erymanthos traveled
into the past

251
00:16:20,431 --> 00:16:22,725
and obliterated
the Iron Tribe's ship

252
00:16:22,725 --> 00:16:24,310
many times over.

253
00:16:24,310 --> 00:16:27,271
But each time,
upon witnessing it,

254
00:16:27,271 --> 00:16:29,523
the fifth's rage only grew.

255
00:16:29,523 --> 00:16:31,900
No matter what path I chose,

256
00:16:31,900 --> 00:16:35,070
Karkinos, Mehitak, and I
all perished

257
00:16:35,070 --> 00:16:36,530
horribly.

258
00:16:36,530 --> 00:16:39,908
Each time,
only the fifth survived.

259
00:16:39,908 --> 00:16:41,493
‐ [gasps]

260
00:16:41,493 --> 00:16:44,371
‐ In the end,
I had to spare the ship

261
00:16:44,371 --> 00:16:46,707
in order to save us.

262
00:16:46,707 --> 00:16:49,918
It was the only way.

263
00:16:49,918 --> 00:16:52,171
Things have to remain
as they are.

264
00:16:52,171 --> 00:16:53,714
Every other possibility
will lead

265
00:16:53,714 --> 00:16:57,259
only to our eventual
destruction,

266
00:16:57,259 --> 00:16:59,887
because the only ones
who can stop him

267
00:16:59,887 --> 00:17:02,431
are on board that ship.

268
00:17:02,431 --> 00:17:07,478
<i>♪ ♪</i>

269
00:17:19,114 --> 00:17:20,783
[liquid squishing]

270
00:17:25,663 --> 00:17:28,791
‐ [gasps]
It can't be.

271
00:17:32,419 --> 00:17:34,046
Why?

272
00:17:46,141 --> 00:17:49,979
You knew... and yet...

273
00:17:49,979 --> 00:17:55,609
<i>♪ ♪</i>

274
00:17:55,609 --> 00:18:00,948
You fought... for us...
all alone.

275
00:18:00,948 --> 00:18:06,996
<i>♪ ♪</i>

276
00:18:08,455 --> 00:18:10,708
I'm so sorry.

277
00:18:10,708 --> 00:18:14,003
Please forgive me, my friend.

278
00:18:14,003 --> 00:18:15,629
<i>♪ ♪</i>

279
00:18:15,629 --> 00:18:17,715
I treated you like a slave,

280
00:18:17,715 --> 00:18:20,592
expecting Bellcross to emerge
whenever he was needed

281
00:18:20,592 --> 00:18:23,637
and not thinking
of what it might do to you.

282
00:18:23,637 --> 00:18:26,473
I made you protect all of us!

283
00:18:26,473 --> 00:18:30,019
You only wanted to please me.

284
00:18:30,019 --> 00:18:33,647
Oh, Age...

285
00:18:33,647 --> 00:18:36,567
I'm so sorry!

286
00:18:53,208 --> 00:18:55,294
My friend.

287
00:19:01,759 --> 00:19:03,469
[gasps]

288
00:19:06,263 --> 00:19:09,308
[Bellcross roars]

289
00:19:11,769 --> 00:19:13,353
Age!

290
00:19:38,837 --> 00:19:40,047
‐ Mehitak and Artemia have lost.

291
00:19:40,047 --> 00:19:42,633
If he lives,
bring him back to me.

292
00:19:42,633 --> 00:19:43,592
‐ Mm...

293
00:19:43,592 --> 00:19:44,885
‐ Let what we have seen here

294
00:19:44,885 --> 00:19:47,179
instruct our next move.

295
00:19:50,474 --> 00:19:51,809
‐ Oh, Mehitak.

296
00:19:56,772 --> 00:19:58,816
‐ What the...

297
00:20:00,484 --> 00:20:02,069
‐ Lecty, what happened?

298
00:20:02,069 --> 00:20:05,239
Was Mehitak able
to calm his rage?

299
00:20:07,407 --> 00:20:10,536
‐ We must return
to Rom Ror's home planet.

300
00:20:10,536 --> 00:20:11,495
‐ And Mehitak?

301
00:20:11,495 --> 00:20:13,413
‐ He has waited a long time

302
00:20:13,413 --> 00:20:15,249
to come face‐to‐face
with a being

303
00:20:15,249 --> 00:20:18,710
that could defeat Artemia
in battle.

304
00:20:18,710 --> 00:20:20,796
We can only hope that now,

305
00:20:20,796 --> 00:20:23,924
freed from his obligation
to the Silver Tribe,

306
00:20:23,924 --> 00:20:26,510
he will be at peace.

307
00:20:28,887 --> 00:20:30,347
‐ Come.

308
00:20:30,347 --> 00:20:31,473
We must leave now.

309
00:20:31,473 --> 00:20:34,852
You and I have contracts
of our own.

310
00:21:00,836 --> 00:21:03,922
[ethereal chiming]

311
00:21:21,857 --> 00:21:23,317
‐ [gasps]

312
00:21:23,317 --> 00:21:26,361
<i>[uplifting music]</i>

313
00:21:26,361 --> 00:21:33,410
<i>♪ ♪</i>

314
00:21:37,623 --> 00:21:40,709
[woman singing in Japanese]

315
00:21:52,304 --> 00:21:54,556
‐ Thank you...

316
00:21:54,556 --> 00:21:56,225
Dhianeila.

317
00:21:56,225 --> 00:21:57,976
‐ [gasps]

318
00:22:01,647 --> 00:22:08,612
<i>♪ ♪</i>

319
00:22:08,612 --> 00:22:11,198
‐ I didn't know where I was.

320
00:22:11,198 --> 00:22:13,700
I couldn't see anything.

321
00:22:20,958 --> 00:22:23,377
There was darkness everywhere.

322
00:22:24,878 --> 00:22:26,421
Then I saw a light.

323
00:22:26,421 --> 00:22:29,508
<i>♪ ♪</i>

324
00:22:29,508 --> 00:22:30,759
You know what?

325
00:22:30,759 --> 00:22:32,386
That light was you.

326
00:22:32,386 --> 00:22:34,429
<i>♪ ♪</i>

327
00:22:34,429 --> 00:22:36,181
‐ Oh, Age.

328
00:23:23,270 --> 00:23:27,065
For me, Age,
you are the light.

329
00:23:27,065 --> 00:23:29,735
You always have been.

330
00:23:29,735 --> 00:23:31,403
Thank you.

331
00:23:33,280 --> 00:23:40,329
<i>♪ ♪</i>

332
00:23:48,795 --> 00:23:50,964
A dark crossroads,
upon which destinies

333
00:23:50,964 --> 00:23:53,967
are forged or broken,
demands a choice be made.

334
00:23:53,967 --> 00:23:55,177
Next time on "Heroic Age,"

335
00:23:55,177 --> 00:23:57,471
episode 16,
"Overcoming the Fates."

